The paper deals with textual network embedding, which involves learning low-dimensional vectorial representations of vertices in a network using rich text information associated with the network. This falls under the scope of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as it specifically deals with NLP and its applications. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category, as the paper deals with network analysis and embedding. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category, as the paper involves learning low-dimensional vectorial representations of vertices using machine learning techniques. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category, as the paper deals with text-related information and its representation in a network. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category, as the paper involves machine learning techniques for text representation and analysis.
